<p>The data used in this post can be found at <a href="https://www.data.gv.at/covid-19/">https://www.data.gv.at/covid-19/</a>. After downloading the CSV file called <code>CovidFaelle_Timeline.csv</code>, we need to do some cleaning of the date column and split off some specific sets - the numbers for Austria, Volarlberg, Tirol and Wien. We also need to format the decimal numbers since the CSV file uses a ',' instead of a '.' as decimal.</p>

<p>First we have the number of cases per 100,000 population across the whole of Austria. After a very sharp rise in cases during the end of October and the middle of November, the number of new cases have fallen due to the second lockdown. At the time of writting, the cases seem to have levelled off a little - though the Austrian government announced a third lockdown lasting a month starting from the 26th of December, in the expectation that cases will continue to rise over the festive period.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
